Invoking: `validate` with `{'patch': '--- a/Modules/_lsprof.c\n+++ b/Modules/_lsprof.c\n@@ -758,10 +758,14 @@\n     while (pObj->currentProfilerContext) {\n         ProfilerContext *pContext = pObj->currentProfilerContext;\n         ProfilerEntry *profEntry= pContext->ctxEntry;\n         if (profEntry)\n             Stop(pObj, pContext, profEntry);\n         else\n-            pObj->currentProfilerContext = pContext->previous;\n-        if (pContext)\n-            PyMem_Free(pContext);\n+            pObj->currentProfilerContext = pContext->previous;\n+        if (pContext) {\n+            ProfilerContext *prev = pContext->previous;\n+            PyMem_Free(pContext);\n+            pObj->currentProfilerContext = prev;\n+            pContext = NULL;\n+        }\n     }\n'}`
responded: The root cause of the use-after-free is in `flush_unmatched`. After freeing `pContext` with `PyMem_Free(pContext);`, the loop does not update `pObj->currentProfilerContext`, so on the next iteration, it tries to access the same (now freed) pointer, leading to a use-after-free.

**Correct fix:**  
After freeing `pContext`, set `pObj->currentProfilerContext` to `pContext->previous` (which is what the code does in the `else` branch, but not after freeing). Also, to be extra safe, set `pContext` to `NULL` after freeing.

Here is the patch:

```diff
--- a/Modules/_lsprof.c
+++ b/Modules/_lsprof.c
@@ -758,10 +758,14 @@
     while (pObj->currentProfilerContext) {
         ProfilerContext *pContext = pObj->currentProfilerContext;
         ProfilerEntry *profEntry= pContext->ctxEntry;
         if (profEntry)
             Stop(pObj, pContext, profEntry);
         else
-            pObj->currentProfilerContext = pContext->previous;
-        if (pContext)
-            PyMem_Free(pContext);
+            pObj->currentProfilerContext = pContext->previous;
+        if (pContext) {
+            ProfilerContext *prev = pContext->previous;
+            PyMem_Free(pContext);
+            pObj->currentProfilerContext = prev;
+            pContext = NULL;
+        }
     }
```

